Step 1) FORK repo in github

Step 2) Clone your forked repo into your local machine 
e.g. $ git clone https://github.com/tunneln/forkedrepo

Step 3) Add the source to your 'remote -v' list. Type 
$ git remote add upstream (source repo http)

Step 4) In order to sync your FORK repo w/ the UPSTREAM (up-to-date) repo. Type 
$ git fetch upstream
$ git checkout master (go into your local master branch)
$ git merge upstream/master (merge from upstream/master into your local master)
